Title: Nutrient Preservation Comparison Study Contact: sarah.perry@water.ca.gov Date: 01/2023

Summary: 2-way paired t-test to determine if theres a significant difference between acidified and frozen samples from Bryte

Read in data

# read in packages
library(tidyverse)
library(stats)
# read in data
df_wq <- read_csv('01_WaterQuality/nutrient-comparison-study/data/nutrient_data.csv')

# mutate df, drop NAs (< RL values)
df_wq <- df_wq %>%
   mutate(Difference = Frozen-Acidified,
          StationType = case_when(
             StationName %in% c('D22','P8','D19','D16 - Twitchell') ~ 'freshwater',
             StationName == 'D7' ~ 'brackish',
             StationName == 'D41' ~ 'saline'
          )) %>%
   drop_na %>%
   pivot_longer(cols = c(Frozen, Acidified),
               names_to = 'PresType',
               values_to = 'Result')

Check boxplot (compared and difference)

First, we look at the individual preservation types to see if there are any outliers

ggplot(df_wq, aes(PresType, Result)) +
  geom_boxplot()+
   facet_wrap(~Analyte)

As we dont see any, we can move on.

The boxplot of the differences gives us a qualitative take on the data.

ggplot(df_wq, aes(,Difference)) +
  geom_boxplot()+
   facet_wrap(~Analyte)

TKN seems to have a higher variance, but a mean close to 0 still. All the rest look okay.

Check normality

for (analyte in unique(df_wq$Analyte)){
   df_test <- df_wq %>% subset(df_wq$Analyte == analyte)
   
   model <- stats::lm(df_test$Result ~ df_test$PresType)
   
   qq_test <- plot(model, pch = 1, frame = FALSE, which = 2)
   title(analyte)
   
   print(qq_test)
}

Residuals arent normal; however, we are assuming we have enough data for the CLT to be valid, and therefore are unconcerned. To be safe, we will also run the model using log-transformed values (which more closely approximate normality):

linear regression

for (analyte in unique(df_wq$Analyte)){
   df_test <- df_wq %>% subset(Analyte == analyte)
   
   df_test_pivot <- df_test %>%
      pivot_wider(names_from = 'PresType',
                  values_from = 'Result')
   
   plt <- ggplot(df_test_pivot, aes(Acidified, Frozen, color = StationType)) +
      geom_point(size=2) +
      geom_smooth(method='lm') +
      theme_bw() +
      facet_wrap(~StationName, scales = 'free') +
      ggtitle(analyte)
   
   print(plt)

   ggsave(paste0('01_WaterQuality/nutrient-comparison-study/plots/lm_',analyte,'.jpg'),
          plot = plt,
          height = 3,
          width = 4.5)
   }

t-test

for (analyte in unique(df_wq$Analyte)){
   df_test <- df_wq %>% subset(Analyte == analyte) 
   
   ttest <- t.test(formula = df_test$Result ~ df_test$PresType,
                   alternative = 'two.sided',
                   mu = 0, 
                   paired = FALSE,   
                   var.equal = FALSE,
                   conf.level = 0.95)
   
   print(paste0('--',analyte,'--'))
   print(ttest)
   }
